Ask HN: Duplicate Real Estate Listings
text:
I live in a city where house prices have been increasing tremendously over the past years. Unfortunately most of the prices are artificially inflated by real estate agencies who sometimes charge even 100k more than the owner’s initial request.

Navigating these listings has proven unnerving to say the least. Especially when multiple agencies post the same property shot from different angles.

I would love to scrape those listings and be able to identify all pictures depicting the same house. The scraping part is easy enough, but how should I proceed with the image grouping/recognition. Is there any trained model that is able to say if the pictures belong to the same house?

Please note that the agencies will not post the exact address and most of the time they will do interior shots only. This prevents the potential buyer to go knock at the owner’s door.

title: Ask HN: Did Chamath Palihapitiya coin/invent the 'data scientist' job role?
text:
In his podcast session with Lex Fridman, Chamath mentions how he coined the term data scientist for a new recruit at Facebook and how that started the whole data scientist role/field.

I was just curious how accurate this is. Was this the first instance of the term? I found it quite interesting

Source: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kFQUDCgMjRc&t=2255s
